Mortality_Analysis

This is a deep analysis of the mortality rate at different levels. It will start with the Statistics of Deaths in Bergamo , Italy. The Excess deaths , compared to historical data, will serve as a proxy to COVID 19 related deaths. The Excess deaths analysis has been published in the past, the following article explains it:

https://towardsdatascience.com/estimating-real-covid-19-death-toll-ef01a5eb9814

and contains a link to the dataset provided by ISTAT.

The focus the following analysis will be on Bergamo. A city of about 1.1 million people in the North of Italy and was the most affected during the pandemic. The assumption, which we expect to validate with comparisons to data from other countries, is that most of the population of this city was exposed directly to the virus. This assumption will serve as a basis to calculate an estimated mortality rate of the virus in that city.

All the files read into the code Chunks can be found in the following public One Drive. If the ready would like to rerun the code, download the files to your computer and change the directory reference in the read.csv functions.

https://1drv.ms/u/s!AqbXNILejy6xh9Mev5jB2ZEz41ypww?e=GgTWek

Germany.Cases = aggregate(Number.of.cases ~ Age.Group, Germany.Data,sum)

Germany.Deaths = aggregate(Number.Death ~ Age.Group, Germany.Data,sum)

#Will merge Cases and Deaths

Germany.Cases.Deaths = merge(Germany.Cases, Germany.Deaths, by = "Age.Group", all.x=TRUE, all.y=FALSE)

#Ration Deaths to confirmed cases

Germany.Cases.Deaths$Ratio.Deaths.Confirmed = Germany.Cases.Deaths$Number.Death / Germany.Cases.Deaths$Number.of.cases

Germany.Cases.Deaths$Ratio.Deaths.Confirmed = round(Germany.Cases.Deaths$Ratio.Deaths.Confirmed,5)

#Adding Percent will be necessary (will have to do the same for Italy)



Germany.Cases.Deaths$Percent = paste(Germany.Cases.Deaths$Ratio.Deaths.Confirmed*100,"%",sep="")

ggplot(Germany.Cases.Deaths, aes(x=Age.Group, y=Ratio.Deaths.Confirmed, fill = Age.Group))+geom_bar(stat="identity") + labs(subtitle="Source: RKI Germany. Based on Confirm Cases and Deaths by Age Group",
         title= "Coronavirus - Germany Ratio of Deaths to Confirmed Cases by Age Group - March to July 29th 2020") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "BrBG") + xlab("Age Group") + ylab("Ratio - Deaths to Confirmed Cases") + geom_text(aes(label=Percent), position=position_dodge(width=0.9), vjust=-0.25)

#Now calculate Ratio Deaths to Confirmed cases
#use max date , it is 6-30

Korea.Age.Ratio = Korea.Age[Korea.Age$date==max(Korea.Age$date),]

Korea.Age.Ratio$Death.Confirmed.Ratio = Korea.Age.Ratio$deceased / Korea.Age.Ratio$confirmed

#Percentage

Korea.Age.Ratio$Percent = paste(round(Korea.Age.Ratio$Death.Confirmed.Ratio,5)*100,"%",sep="")

ggplot(Korea.Age.Ratio, aes(x=age, y=Death.Confirmed.Ratio, fill = age))+geom_bar(stat="identity") + labs(subtitle="Source: Korea Centers for Disease Control. Based on Confirm Cases and Deaths by Age Group",

Load Singapore Data to do analysis by Age Group not that many cases and not new information

Singapore.Age = read.csv("C:/Users/figue/Documents/Coronavirus/Mortality_Study/Singapore_Age.csv",stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
#will group in Age by 10s 0-9; 10-19 etc... to match to Germany and South Korea
#Status. Aggregate by Age and Status
#Let's use cut for grouping


#Age is character type
#first change to numeric to coerce NAs
Singapore.Age$Age=as.numeric(Singapore.Age$Age)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
#remove 31 NAs

Singapore.Age = Singapore.Age[!is.na(Singapore.Age$Age),]

#Add age grouping name

Singapore.Age$Age_Group = paste((Singapore.Age$Age %/% 10)*10,"s",sep="")
#total cases by group
Singapore.Summary = aggregate(Case ~ Age_Group, data= Singapore.Age, length)

#There are only 11 Deceased

#Calculate divisor for Germany and Korea based on population above 60. More than 300 confirmed cases in Singapore
#Germany and Korea most likely did not confirm all covid cases

Midpoint.Germany = sum(Confirmed.Cases.Deaths[Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Country=="Germany" & (Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A80+" | Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A60-A79"),"Ratio.death.case"])/2

Midpoint.Korea = sum(Confirmed.Cases.Deaths[Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Country=="South Korea" & (Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A80+" | Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A60-A79"),"Ratio.death.case"])/2

Midpoint.Singapore = sum(Confirmed.Cases.Deaths[Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Country=="Singapore" & (Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A80+" | Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Age.Group == "A60-A79"),"Ratio.death.case"])/2

Divisor.Germany = Midpoint.Germany/Midpoint.Singapore
Divisor.Korea = Midpoint.Korea/Midpoint.Singapore

Divisor.Germany

Divisor.Korea
## [1] 2.361695

Confirmed.Cases.Deaths[ Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Country=="Germany","Ratio.death.case2"] = Confirmed.Cases.Deaths[Confirmed.Cases.Deaths$Country=="Germany","Ratio.death.case"]/Divisor.Germany
